National Meeting Held to Commemorate Day of Sun 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- A national meeting was held at Pyongyang Indoor Stadium Saturday with large attendance to commemorate the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam, member of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, made a report. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the birth of Kim Il Sung was a majestic sunrise as it brought the dawn of national resurrection to the Korean people suffering from the statelessness and promised a new spring to humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President is a peerlessly great man and outstanding leader whom the Korean nation has acclaimed for the first time in the nation's history spanning more than thousands of years and a gifted thinker and theoretician who fathered the immortal Juche idea that holds the highest and most shining position in human history of thought and ushered in the new era of history, the Juche era, the reporter said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Il Sung is an outstanding leader and iron-willed commander who started the Songun revolution and led the cause of independence against imperialism to victory under the banner of the Juche idea, thus saving the destiny of the country and the nation and glorifying it with arms. He is a peerless statesman who built a powerful driving force for the revolution and a genius of creation and construction and father of socialist Korea as he built Korean-style socialism centered on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Brilliantly recorded in his glorious history of revolutionary leadership are the precious feats he performed through his tireless activities for the reunification of the country and the independence of the whole world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His revolutionary idea and feats have been firmly preserved and successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il, illustrious commander born of Mt. Paektu, has pursued the Songun politics by developing in depth the Songun idea and line of Juche which have been consistently applied in the whole course of the Korean revolution. This has served as a fundamental source for the Korean revolution to make miraculous victories generation after generation despite manifold difficulties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter called on all the party members, servicepersons and people to firmly uphold and thoroughly embody the President's idea and line and the glorious revolutionary traditions of the WPK and on all fields and units to implement his last instructions to the letter. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to wage a strenuous struggle for the independent reunification of the country under the slogan "Add brilliance to the June 15 era of reunification by attaching importance to the nation, defending peace and achieving unity" and steadily boost international support and solidarity for the Korean revolutionary cause in the idea of independence, peace and friendship, the reporter noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and people of the DPRK will closely follow the moves of the U.S. and its allied forces including Japan with a high degree of revolutionary vigilance and firmly defend their ideology, system and just cause by firmly increasing the political and military might of the DPRK under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending the meeting were senior party, army and state officials and working people in Pyongyang, a delegation of the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front, and delegations of overseas Koreans in various regions including the delegation of Koreans in Japan and overseas compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were the visiting delegations and delegates of different countries, diplomatic envoys of different countries and representatives of international bodies here, and other foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Similar meetings were held at all provinces, cities and counties across the country.

Floral Tribute Paid to Statues of Kim Il Sung 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Floral baskets were laid before the statues of President Kim Il Sung across the country on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Servicepersons, working people from all walks of life and school youth and children in Pyongyang visited the statue of the President on Mansu Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Standing before the statue of Kim Il Sung was a floral basket sent by General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets and bouquets were placed before his statue in the name of the party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions and KPA units, institutions of science, education, culture and art, public health and media, industrial establishments, farms and schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also put in front of the statue were floral baskets in the name of the Pyongyang Mission of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front and overseas compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Floral baskets and bouquets were also laid before the statues of Kim Il Sung at Kim Il Sung University, Kim Il Sung Military University, the Ministry of People's Security, the Pyongyang Schoolchildren's Palace and other places of the city and in different places of the country.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from AINDF Central Committee 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a letter from the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front Sunday, the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The birth of President Kim Il Sung was a great fortune for the Koreans as they acclaimed a peerlessly great man for the first time in the history spanning five thousand years and a historic event in which the dawn of the era of independence broke for the Korean nation and humankind, the letter said, noting that his whole life was the great one of a legendary great man who performed the undying feats for the liberation and independence of the country and the bright future of the nation and humankind. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President founded the immortal Juche idea, ushering in a new era of history in which the working people were shaping their destiny independently, it said, stressing that he was a benefactor of the nation's resurrection and iron-willed brilliant commander who hewed the road of the unique Songun revolution and successfully pursued the line of attaching importance to the army and military affairs to defeat the two formidable enemies, the U.S. and Japanese imperialists, and the father of socialist Korea who built a powerful country, independent in politics, self-supporting in economy and self-reliant in national defence in the north by successfully leading the two-stage social revolution, two-time rehabilitation and several-stage socialist construction with his extraordinary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's successful solution to the issue of succeeding to the leadership is brilliantly shining as an exploit to be specially recorded in history because he enabled the Koreans to become a nation blessed with the illustrious leaders down through generations, the letter said, noting that he, endowed with the idea of loving the country, the nation and the people, considered the reunification of the country as the supreme task of the nation, worked heart and soul for its implementation till the last moments of his life, put forward the three charters of national reunification,  arousing all the fellow countrymen to their materialization and opening up a bright prospect of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's revolutionary cause has been successfully carried forward by you and the President's history is being given steady continuity generation after generation, it said, stressing that Kim Jong Il firmly defended the country, the nation and socialism of Juche by shattering every attempt of the U.S.-led imperialist allied forces to stifle the DPRK with his invincible Songun politics and launched a dynamic drive for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation despite unprecedented difficulties and ordeals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A particular mention should be made of the fact that you put the north on the position of a matchless nation and put forward the Korean nation as a powerful nation which no one dares provoke with your iron will and energetic Songun revolutionary leadership, it said, describing it as a great jubilee to be specially recorded in the nation's history spanning five thousand years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vanguard fighters and patriotic people from all walks life in the south are fully determined to glorify for all ages the revolutionary career and feats of the President and implement his instructions on national reunification to the letter, cherishing the greatest fortune and honor of having you as the top leader of the nation, the letter concluded.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il from Secretary General of IIJI 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a floral basket by Kenichi Ogami, secretary general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, and his party on a visit to the DPRK on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general handed the floral basket to an official concerned on Saturday.

Regional Seminar on Juche Idea Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- A seminar of Eastern Europe and Central Asia on the Juche idea was held in Sankt-Peterburg, Russia, on April 7 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were I. G. Chernishenko and V. Tsulkin, deputies to the Russian State Duma, Alfred Petrovich, Latvian lawmaker, Mikhail Panchenko, general secretary of the International Federation of the Associations for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Songun Policy in Eastern Europe and Central Asia, and representatives of organizations for the study of the Juche idea and the Songun policy and people in different countries including Russia, Ukraine, Belarus and Kazakhstan and regions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Mikhail Panchenko made a report to be followed by congratulatory speeches by some personages at the seminar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporter and speakers underlined the urgent need for each country and region to apply the Juche idea and the Songun idea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that the Juche idea indicates the way to be followed by humankind as the guiding idea of the present times and represents the firm faith of all the progressive people in their struggle for independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration adopted at the seminar noted that the revolutionary history of President Kim Il Sung is the history of the Songun leadership and serves as a torchlight illumining the way of achieving the emancipation and prosperity of the oppressed and maltreated people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration called for expanding the ranks of adherents to the Juche idea, the Songun idea and more dynamically conducting the study and dissemination of the Juche idea and the Songun idea in various forms and by diverse methods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The declaration stressed that no force can stop the people from equipping themselves with the Juche idea and the Songun idea and dynamically advancing towards a new just world free from exploitation and oppression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A letter to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the seminar.

Important Days of DPRK Commemorated in Foreign Countries  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The round-table talks took place in Egypt, a meeting in Denmark and lectures in India and Democratic Congo from April 3 to 5 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun and the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Wahid Al Uksouri, chairman of the Misr Arab Socialist Party of Egypt, said that socialism in the DPRK would grow stronger and the world socialist movement dynamically advance as long as there is the leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anders Kristensen, chairman of the Denmark-DPRK Friendship Association, noted that the world progressive people are highly praising President Kim Il Sung as the most prominent state leader representing the 20th century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Balzor Singh Chauhan, chairman of the Indian Youth Group for the Study of Works of Comrade Kim Il Sung, said that thanks to the powerful military muscle provided by Kim Il Sung the army and the people of the DPRK have been able to stand calm and composed and confident in the showdown with the U.S. styling itself the world's "only superpower." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Denmark. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, a Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibition was held at the Cuban Revolutionary Museum from April 6 to 13 under the co-sponsorship of the Cuban Institute of Friendship with the Peoples and the Cuban Committee for Supporting Korea's Reunification on the occasion of the Day of the Sun.

Reception Given at DPRK Embassy  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The DPRK embassy in Moscow arranged a reception on April 12 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Alexandr Saltanov, Russian vice-foreign minister, Chilgichi Chimit Ondar, chairman of the Russia-DPRK friendship parliamentary group of the State Duma of Russia, and Josif Kobzon, chairman of the Cultural Committee of the State Duma of Russia, and officials of the government, political parties and organizations including the Foreign Ministry, the Ministry of Defense, the Party for Peace and Unity of Russia, the Communist Party of the Russian Federation, the All-Union Communist Party of Bolsheviks, the Communist Party of the Soviet Union, the "Peace and Today" Committee of Russia, the Russian War Veterans' Committee, the Association of Scientists for the Study of Human Affairs in the Present World, the Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK and the Russian Youth Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and officials in the fields of science, education, culture and art and media including the Institute of Oriental Studies and the Institute of the Far East of the Russian Academy of Sciences, the State Academic Moiseyev Dance Company, the State Academy Ensemble of Ministry of Interior of Russia, the Moscow Tchaikovsky State Conservatory, the Russian Newspaper Patriot, ITAR-TASS and Ria-Novosti News Agency. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ambassador Kim Yong Jae and staff members of the DPRK embassy were on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants laid a floral basket and bouquets before the full-length painting portraying President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il and paid tribute to them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Russian vice-foreign minister said in his speech at the reception that feats of Kim Il Sung, a prominent statesman who laid a foundation of the Russia-DPRK friendship and worked heart and soul for the development of the friendly relations between the two countries to the last moments of his life, will always be recorded in history.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il from Russian Figures 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with gifts by the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia and the Public Chamber of the All-Russia Business Union "Business Russia".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were handed to Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, on Saturday by Alexey Mitrofanov, member of the Supreme Council of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia and vice-chairman of the Committee on Constitutional Legislation and State System of the State Duma of the Russian Federation who is heading the party delegation, and Boris Titov, chairman of the Public Chamber of the All-Russia Business Union "Business Russia" on a visit to the DPRK to commemorate the Day of the Sun.

Delegations and Delegates of Juche Idea Study Organizations Feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The government of the DPRK gave a reception for delegations and delegates of organizations for the study of the Juche idea at Pyongyang Koryo Hotel Saturday on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present on invitation were Vishwanath, director general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, Kenichi Ogami, secretary general of the IIJI, and his party, delegations and delegates of Juche idea study organizations in various countries on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, in a speech said that the feats performed by President Kim Il Sung are shining long with the century, adding that organizations for the study of the Juche idea and its followers are on the steady increase and activities are brisk worldwide to study and disseminate the idea and apply it to the specific conditions of their countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that the Korean people will always stand on the side of the Juche idea followers in the drive to achieve the independent development of the country and the nation and the cause of global independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking next, Vishwanath said that the Day of the Sun, the birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung, a great man whom humankind acclaimed, is a holiday common to the progressive people, adding that the President built a socialist country in Korea to which the world looks up and provided an all-powerful treasured sword for the victory of the cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the 20th century was shining with the august name of the President, he said that the DPRK has turned into a powerful and prosperous country thanks to Kim Jong Il who is implementing the President's behests.

Order Awarded to Mass Gymnastic and Artistic Performance "Arirang"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century" awarded the "Peace" order and its certificate to the mass gymnastic and artistic performance "Arirang." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were conveyed to Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, by President Oleg Oleinik, who is heading the delegation of the fund on a visit to the DPRK, at the May Day Stadium on Saturday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Hong Son Ok, vice-chairwoman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries who is chairwoman of the DPRK-Russia Friendship Association, officials concerned and members of the delegation of the fund.

Concluded FTA Declared Null and Void 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Members of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification, the People for Achieving Peace and Reunification, the "National Congress for Independent and Peaceful Reunification" and other civic and public organizations in south Korea reportedly held the 91st anti-U.S. solidarity meeting near the U.S. embassy in Seoul on April 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made and then a resolution was read out at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution declared totally null and void the concluded south Korea-U.S. "Free Trade Agreement" as it will leave the south Korean economy to the tender mercy of the U.S. and drive the people to destitution &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution accused the "government" of setting in motion conservative media and its stooges to launch a large-scale offensive for building up public opinion in a bid to hide the flunkeyist and traitorous nature of FTA after its conclusion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It declared that the above-said organizations would make every possible effort to seek the nullification of humiliating FTA which is full of lies to deceive the people and aimed to force on south Korea an unlimited drain on its resources for the U.S. and get the present "government" step down.

Gifts to Kim Jong Il from International Juche Idea Study Organizations 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the International Institute of the Juche Idea on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was presented with a gift by visiting Vishwanath, its director general on the same occasion. The gifts were handed to an official concerned by Vishwanath.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il was also presented with a floral basket and a gift by the delegation of the Japanese Society for the Study of Kimilsungism on a visit to the DPRK and with a gift by the visiting Norwegian delegation for the Study of the Juche Idea.

Day of Sun Editorially Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Papers today dedicate editorials to the 95th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says that the President, possessed of gifted qualification and distinguished personality, performed the undying feats on behalf of the era and history by leading the Korean revolution and the human cause of independence to victory for a long period. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His revolutionary history is a glorious history of a peerlessly great man who performed the undying feats for the country, the nation, the era and revolution, regarding it as his lifelong mission to build a prosperous and powerful country, the daily notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of his revolutionary leadership is a brilliant history of a peerlessly great man who indicated the way of building a powerful socialist country with his gifted ideas, theories and wisdom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He founded the Juche idea, an undying revolutionary banner in the era of independence, and provided an eternal cornerstone for building a powerful socialist country of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He clarified the way of building a prosperous and powerful country in every period and at each stage of the developing revolution with his rare intelligence and extraordinary clairvoyance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of his revolutionary leadership is a history of struggle of a distinguished genius who built a prospering socialist country on this land with his iron will, experienced and tested leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also a history of sacred struggle of a peerless patriot who provided the country and people with an eternal foundation to win one victory after another. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an immortal history of a rare statesman who demonstrated before the world the dignity of the country and the nation with his absolute authority. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His cause of building a powerful socialist nation has been successfully carried forward and accelerated thanks to the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il set an epoch-making example in accomplishing the cause of perpetuating the memory of the President, developed the Party, the army and the state into his ones and made sure that his history of building a glorious rich and powerful nation is given steady continuity. Kim Jong Il's noble sense of revolutionary obligation is touching the whole world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the fixed will of Kim Jong Il to accomplish with the might of Songun the cause of building a rich and powerful nation pioneered by the President under the banner of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il unrolled a clear blueprint for building a great prosperous powerful nation, visualizing the future of the country with his clairvoyant wisdom and far-sightedness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His grandiose plan for building a great prosperous powerful nation and energetic leadership are arousing all the servicepersons and people to creation and innovations; his plan and leadership serve as a source that encourages them to make a leaping forward on all fronts of building a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President's feats performed for the building of a rich and powerful nation will shine long century after century and he will be immortal as the sun of humankind thanks to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson calls upon all the people to unite around Kim Jong Il single-mindedly and dynamically advance to achieve the prosperity of Kim Il Sung's Korea holding high the great banner of Songun.

Senior Officials Pay Homage to Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Senior party, army and state officials, the chairman of a friendly party, Cabinet members and leading officials of party, armed forces and power organs, public organizations, ministries and national institutions visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace Sunday to pay homage to President Kim Il Sung on the occasion of his 95th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amidst the solemn playing of "Song of General Kim Il Sung" a floral basket was laid before his statue in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea, the National Defence Commission of the DPRK, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants paid high tribute to his statue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They entered the hall where he lies in state and paid homage to him in humble reverence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They went round orders, medals and certificates of honorary titles awarded to him in the DPRK and different countries. They also looked round the portrait of the smiling President and bronze relievos in the Mourning Hall, a train coach and a car he used. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Anti-Japanese revolutionary fighters, officials of institutions at different levels, servicepersons and people of all strata visited the memorial palace on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The diplomatic corps and the military attaches' corps here, the delegation of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia, the delegation of the Workers' Party of Mexico, the delegation of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century", the director general and the secretary general of the International Institute of the Juche Idea, the delegations of organizations for the study of the Juche idea from different countries and foreign guests, overseas compatriots including the delegation of Koreans in Japan, families of those related to the anti-Japanese Revolutionary struggle in China and families of the Chinese related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle visited the Kumsusan Memorial Palace on Sunday to pay homage to the President.

Children's Camping Begins
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- The first-term camping this year began with due ceremonies at the children's union camps in different parts of the country including those in Mangyongdae, Lake Yonphung, Haeju, Soho and Kyongpho and the Songdowon International Children's Union Camp on Saturday and Sunday on the occasion of the significant Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reporters and speakers at the ceremonies referred to the children's pleasure of participating in the first-term camping against the background of the commemoration of the nation's greatest April holiday, adding that all the campers should learn from the brilliant boyhood of the peerlessly great men and take an active part in study tour, mountaineering and sports activities during the camping to train their bodies and minds and consolidate what they have learned at schools. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Officials of provinces, cities and counties congratulated the campers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They spent the first pleasant day of camping with colorful sports and amusement games and entertainment programs.

Kim Yong Nam Meets Foreign Guests 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a friendly talk with Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, on a visit to the DPRK to commemorate the Day of the Sun at the Mansudae Assembly Hall Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand was Kim Thae Jong, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Yong Nam also met and had a cordial talk with a delegation of the Russian International Charity Fund "Protectors of Arts for the Century" led by President Oleg Oleinik on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, Mun Jae Chol, acting chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, Kung Sok Ung, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, officials concerned and Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Valery Sukhinin.

Letter to Kim Jong Il from Participants in Joint TV Gathering
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a letter from the participants in a joint TV gathering to commemorate the Day of the Sun on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter said that President Kim Il Sung is highly praised by all people as the great sun of humankind for the undying feats he performed on behalf of the era and history by wisely leading the Korean revolution and the human cause of independence with rare wisdom, outstanding leadership ability and noble virtues. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Staying in the DPRK, we have learned that the cause of Juche, the cause of Songun pioneered by the President is being successfully inherited and carried out generation after generation under your energetic leadership, the letter said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Progressive humankind highly praise you as a champion of justice and peace and the great sun of the 21st century as you are fully demonstrating the might of heroic Korea and its invincible mettle with your ever-victorious Songun politics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will do our best to support Songun Korea, entrusting to you the future of the human cause of independence in the future, too, as we have worked as ardent adherents to the great idea of the President, attracted by his personality as a great man, and active supporters to the cause of the Korean people in the past. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bright is the future of progressive humankind and the heroic struggle of the Korean people for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and the reunification of the country is sure to win as it is guided by you.

Friendly Picnic Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 15 (KCNA) -- A friendly picnic of participants in the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival took place at the Rungrado Recreation Ground Sunday to commemorate the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Participants were divided into the "Friendship" team and "Peace" team before having amusement games. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the turn of each game, the acrobats showed their skills and cheering groups of students and children presented dances, etc., adding to the atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After the end of the games foreign and overseas Korean artistes and Korean school youth and children pleasantly danced to the tune of music.

Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il Praised
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Hasanul Huq Inu, chairman of the Central Executive Committee of the Bangladesh National Socialist Party, made public a statement on April 12 on the occasion of the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He in his statement noted that the great events and brilliant successes recorded in the modern history of Korea would be unthinkable apart from the august name of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These instill great confidence and courage into the world progressive people in their struggle to build an independent and prosperous new society, he said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, released a statement on April 9 on the occasions of the Day of the Sun, the 14th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's election as chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission and the 75th anniversary of the heroic Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He stressed that Korea, the sun's country shining with the august names of the peerlessly great men, will always prosper together with the Juche idea and the majestic appearance of Korean-style socialism.

DPRK Government's Struggle for Reunification Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- The Maldivian government fully supports the DPRK government's struggle to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country in the idea of "By our nation itself." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Maldivian President Maumoon Abdul Gayoom said this when receiving credentials from the DPRK ambassador e.p. to Maldives on April 9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling his visit to the DPRK in 1983, he praised steersman of the DPRK Kim Jong Il as a prominent statesman and great leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that Maldives and the DPRK opened the friendly and cooperative relations long ago and have since developed them, he noted that it is the invariable stand of the government and the people of Maldives to boost them.

Performances of Art Festival Go on with Success 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Third-day performances and separate performances of the 25th April Spring Friendship Art Festival were given on April 13. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kazakh female solo "Our Happiness Blossoms Out under the Leader's Care," mixed duet "Our Leader" presented by the Belarusan musical company, male solo "Long Live Generalissimo Kim Il Sung" by the art troupe of Koreans in China and other numbers highly lauded the great feats of President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Indonesian Guruhsukarno Dancing Troupe, the art troupe of Koreans in the U.S. and other art groups put on the stages female solo "Kimilsungia in Full Bloom All Over the World," "We Pledge," fourth movement of the symphony "Leader Will Always Be with Us," and other numbers which made a successful artistic representation of the firm belief that President Kim Il Sung will always be with progressive humankind and his last instructions are sure to come true. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The art troupes of Koreans in Japan and China truthfully represented their desire and will to grandly commemorate the April spring holiday through the numbers such as "Let's Present Songs and Dances on Stage of Spring Festival" and "We Sing of the Day of the Sun." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dance "Katyusha" presented by the Tap dancers troupe of Russia, instrumental ensemble "Souvenir" by the "Pereprava" musical company of Russia, "Dance of Greetings" by the "Zoryane" song and dance ensemble of Ukraine, song and dance "Sleeve" by the Tajik art troupe, "Peacock Dance" by the Indian folk dance troupe, a folk dance by the Egyptian "Vuhaihra" folk dance troupe and other numbers successfully dealt with the emotion, mental world, lifestyle, the diligent labor and traditions of their peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Acrobats of Russia, China, Mongolia, Bulgaria, Sweden, Ukraine and Japan put on the stage "Dexterity at Caps," "Wit of Standing on One Hand," "Aerial Stunt," "Two Men's Stunt," "Male and Female Aerial Stunt," "Playing on Rope," "Manual Dexterity," "Mysterious Fingers" and other numbers, impressing the spectators with dynamic and witty techniques and refined movements. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
