&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, April 14 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Saturday sent a congratulatory message to So Man Sul, chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon), on his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim in the message said that So is an ardent patriot and a tested activist of the overseas Koreans movement who, true to President Kim Il Sung's Juche-oriented idea on the movement and leadership over it, has devoted all his life to the prosperity of the socialist homeland, the independent reunification of Korea and the strengthening of the patriotic cause of Chongryon and the protection of the national rights of Koreans in Japan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The more than half a century-long history of Chongryon, during which it has demonstrated itself as a pioneer of the patriotic movement, a model of patriotic devotion and a model of overseas Koreans movement, is associated with the devoted service and great feats you have made for the homeland and the nation, Chongryon and the Koreans in Japan, the message said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim wished So good health and happiness, hoping that he would achieve greater success in his responsible work for developing Chongryon and the movement of Koreans in Japan on a new higher stage.

